hings, that one told Joseph, Behold, thy father is sick: and he took with him his two sons, Manasseh and Ephraim.","year":-1689},{"id":"recRA8VnSMafa9oPB","ref":"Gen.48.2","text":"And one told Jacob, and said, Behold, thy son Joseph cometh unto thee: and Israel strengthened himself, and sat upon the bed.","year":-1689},{"id":"rechacd9J6TOZj62V","ref":"Gen.48.3","text":"And Jacob said unto Joseph, God Almighty appeared unto me at Luz in the land of Canaan, and blessed me,","year":-1689},{"id":"rec4EsgNsXyweeG0A","ref":"Gen.48.4","text":"And said unto me, Behold, I will make thee fruitful, and multiply thee, and I will make of thee a multitude of people; and will give this land to thy seed after thee for an everlasting possession.","year":-1689},{"id":"reciPdJ1UsgShHHOA","ref":"Gen.48.5","text":"And now thy two sons, Ephraim and Manasseh, which were born unto thee in the land of Egypt before I came unto thee into Egypt, are mine; as Reuben and Simeon, they shall be mine.","year":-1689},{"id":"rec1HiU9evE0JEniq","ref":"Gen.48.6","text":"And thy issue, which thou begettest after them, shall be thine, and shall be called after the name of their brethren in their inheritance.","year":-1689},{"id":"rec35IAotqDybHnI1","ref":"Gen.48.7","text":"And as for me, when I came from Padan, Rachel died by me in the land of Canaan in the way, when yet there was but a little way to come unto Ephrath: and I buried her there in the way of Ephrath; the same is Bethlehem.","year":-1689},{"id":"recEW34uA8UlUWNc1","ref":"Gen.48.8","text":"And Israel beheld Joseph’s sons, and said, Who are these?","year":-1689}]}
